Ipid is investigating an alleged police brutality incident at the Lentegeur police station. CAPE TOWN - The Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid) is investigating an alleged police brutality incident at the Lentegeur police station.The incident, which occurred on Saturday evening, was filmed and subsequently surfaced on Facebook.The video showcases a woman getting into a scuffle with an officer.WATCH: Altercation at police station gets physicalIt is alleged the woman was at the police station to report a robbery.Ipid spokesperson Moses Dlamini says: We became aware of it on Monday. It hasn t been reported but we ve since received a docket and we re investigating. The 23-year-old woman was charged with crimen injuria and resisting arrest.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)